  programs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618050Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23820-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Computers follow instructions called programs to perform tasks."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618054Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23820-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Programs tell the computer how to process data, such as numbers, text, or
  images."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618061Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23820-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A general-purpose computer can run many different programs, unlike a single-purpose
  device, which is built for one job."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618065Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23876-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Hacking, in the context of cybersecurity, is gaining unauthorised access to, or
  control of, a computer system."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618971Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23876-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The Computer Misuse Act 1990 defines what is considered as unlawful access to
  computer systems."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618975Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23876-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "DDOS attacks can be used to disrupt online services."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618981Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23876-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A brute force attack is a trial and error process to gain access to protected
  resources."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:29.618987Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-23879-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
